                <p>Suzuki Motorcycle India has officially launched the new GSX-8R at a price of ₹9.25 lakh (ex-showroom). The GSX-8R is a middleweight sportbike designed for those seeking a blend of daily usability and high-performance thrills. As part of Suzuki’s iconic GSX lineup, this latest addition aims to appeal to sportbike enthusiasts who value technology, performance, and sleek design.</p>
                <p>The Suzuki GSX-8R comes with an 800cc parallel-twin engine capable of delivering impressive power, ensuring an exhilarating riding experience. The engine produces around 82 PS of peak power at 8500 rpm and a maximum torque of 78 Nm at 6800 rpm. The bike is equipped with a 6-speed manual transmission featuring a bi-directional quick-shifter for a smooth and engaging ride.</p>
                <p>In terms of design, the GSX-8R embodies Suzuki’s aggressive sports styling with sharp aerodynamic fairings, a split LED headlamp setup, and an aerodynamic windshield for reduced wind resistance. The digital instrument cluster provides a range of useful data, including speed, fuel levels, gear position, and more, contributing to a highly user-friendly experience. With its fully-adjustable KYB front forks and a monoshock rear suspension, the GSX-8R is built for stability, performance, and comfort, both on the track and regular roads.</p>
                <p>Additional features include dual-channel ABS, multiple riding modes, and traction control, ensuring safety at all speeds. The dual-disc front brakes and single-disc rear brake provide exceptional braking power, which is critical for spirited riding. The GSX-8R is also equipped with lightweight alloy wheels and tubeless radial tyres for excellent grip and handling.</p>
                <p>The launch of the GSX-8R at ₹9.25 lakh places it in direct competition with other popular middleweight sportbikes, offering a compelling package of performance, technology, and iconic Suzuki reliability.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Features and Specifications:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine:</span> 800cc, parallel-twin, liquid-cooled.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Power Output:</span> 82 PS @@ 8500 rpm.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Torque:</span> 78 Nm @@ 6800 rpm.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Transmission:</span> 6-speed manual with bi-directional quick-shifter.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Suspension:</span> KYB fully adjustable front forks, monoshock rear suspension.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Brakes:</span> Dual front disc brakes, single rear disc brake, dual-channel ABS.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Tyres:</span> Radial, tubeless.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Riding Modes:</span> Multiple riding modes with adjustable traction control.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Lighting:</span> Full LED lighting including headlamps, tail lamps, and indicators.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Instrument Console:</span> Fully digital with multiple readouts like gear position, fuel levels, and trip data.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

